&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOUCESTERSHIRE HOSPITALS NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-time Consultant Breast Radiologist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(part-time will be considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Consultant Breast Radiologist to join the existing imaging team at Thirlestaine Breast Centre, Gloucestershire NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a replacement post and both full/part-time working would be considered. The successful candidate will also have the opportunity to contribute to a couple of general radiology sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to have experience in breast imaging in both the screening and symptomatic settings. This includes the reporting of mammograms, breast ultrasound, stereotactic and ultrasound guided biopsies/wire localisations and breast MRI. Some experience of cross-sectional oncological imaging is also desirable, though not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both the breast screening and symptomatic services are based at Thirlestaine Breast Centre, Cheltenham. This is a purpose-built integrated unit, operational since October 2009, separate from the main Cheltenham General Hospital site. It is a fully equipped Screening Unit with 4 new FFDM units, 2 with stereotactic capability and tomosynthesis, one of which also has contrast enhanced spectral mammography. There are three ultrasound units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two FFDM-equipped mobile units provide screening for clients at other sites in Gloucestershire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate would be joining a team of 3 consultant radiologists, 2 breast clinicians and 1 consultant radiographer. The unit is actively involved in role extension with Advanced Practice Radiographers performing film reading, ultrasound and image guided breast biopsy. Screening MRI is undertaken in the Cheltenham Imaging Centre adjacent to the Breast Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively participate in audit and research and are currently undertaking clinical trials involving Contrast Enhanced Spectral mammography, digital breast tomosynthesis and breast MRI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cheltenham is a large Regency town renowned for its music, literary and cricket festivals and for the ‘Cheltenham Gold Cup’. Gloucestershire is well known for its cultural and leisure activities and has many excellent state and private schools as well as colleges of higher education and its own university (the University of Gloucestershire).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Dr Sarah Vinnicombe (Consultant Breast Radiologist) on 0300 422 3778.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply, please visit NHS jobs. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;You should also attach a CV to your online application form. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
